result.notes:
The Council publishes details of every transaction on Government Procurement Cards. The reports are available in comma delimited format (CSV) and PDF format, and are listed by month at the bottom.
Invitations to tender (ITTs)
The Council publishes details to tender for contracts to provide goods, works and services on the North East Procurement Organisation (NEPO) Electronic Tendering Portal at www.nepoportal.org This link will take you directly to the North East Procurement Organisation Portal's home page where all 12 North East Councils advertise their procurement opportunities.
In order to see Newcastle's specific opportunities please follow this process:

  Click on 'Current Opportunities';
  Click on 'Search Latest Opportunities';
  Select 'Newcastle City Council' from the Organisation dropdown box;
  Then click the Search tab. This will display all opportunites that are open to all suppliers.

Contracts register
Details of all current contracts which the Council has either awarded directly or participates in is published on the NEPO Portal at www.nepoportal.org
The contract register includes details of all contracts, commissioned activity and framework agreements. As new contracts are awarded the contracts register is automatically updated. 
In order to view Newcastle's contracts please follow this process:

  Under the links section on the left of th Home Page click on the 'Contract Register';
  Under 'Choose Sub Region' select Tyne and Wear'
  Under 'Choose Council to view' select 'Newcastle City Council'

Purchase orders with the value of £5,000 - £25,000
The reports are available in comma delimited format (CSV) and are listed by quarter at the bottom.
Waste collection contracts
The council undetakes its statutory (refuse and recucling) and optional (garden waste) waste collections in-house and does not contract out to a third party for any of these collections.
Doing business with the Council
If you would like to see how you can do business with the council or require any other procurement related information, then please visit our procurement page titles Tenders Contracts and Procurement.
Further information
Please go to: https://www.newcastle.gov.uk/your-council-and-democracy/open-data-and-access-to-information/local-transparency/local-transparency-procurement
